RACE.FOOTNOTES: STORM IN THE VALLE tracked the early pace, raced four wide through the turn, took control mid stretch, drifted out and was best today. WAY TO RULE was unhurried early, advanced five wide through the turn, was gaining steadily, was forced out late stretch by the winner and finished second best. ISABEL LOVE pressed the early pace, raced along the inside through the turn, weakened late stretch and was along for third. FAUZETA'S FLAME set a pressured early pace, raced three wide into the turn and gave way. STORM CENT was up close early, raced four wide and faded. QUEEN HADASSAH was allowed to settle early, raced six wide and gave way. MISS WONDERFUL raced in mid pack early, went three wide and flattened out. NEXT REYNA was void of any early speed, raced four wide through the turn and offered no late rally. VIPER VIXEN was outrun early from the inside and never fired. THE STEWARDS POSTED AN INQUIRY INTO AN INCIDENT INVOLVINT THE TOP TWO FINISHERS IN THE STRETCH DRIVE AND TOOK NO ACTION. Race was Hand Timed.
